# PostgreSQL CRUD Cheat Sheet ðŸ˜ (Basic Commands)

Simple **CRUD** (Create, Read, Update, Delete) + common extras.

---

## 1) CREATE âœ… (Table + Insert)

### Create Table

```sql
CREATE TABLE users (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(150) UNIQUE,
  age INT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### Insert Row

```sql
INSERT INTO users (name, email, age)
VALUES ('Clint', 'clint@gmail.com', 20);
```

---

## 2) READ âœ… (SELECT)

### Select All

```sql
SELECT * FROM users;
```

### Select Specific Columns

```sql
SELECT name, email FROM users;
```

### Select With Condition

```sql
SELECT * FROM users WHERE age >= 18;
```

### Select One Row (by ID)

```sql
SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1;
```

### Sort Results

```sql
SELECT * FROM users ORDER BY id DESC;
```

### Limit Rows

```sql
SELECT * FROM users LIMIT 5;
```

---

## 3) UPDATE âœ…

### Update One Column

```sql
UPDATE users
SET age = 21
WHERE id = 1;
```

### Update Multiple Columns

```sql
UPDATE users
SET name = 'New Name',
    email = 'new@gmail.com'
WHERE id = 1;
```

---

## 4) DELETE âœ…

### Delete One Row

```sql
DELETE FROM users WHERE id = 1;
```

### Delete All Rows (Table stays)

```sql
DELETE FROM users;
```

---

# Extra Useful Commands âš¡

### Drop Table (Deletes table completely)

```sql
DROP TABLE users;
```

### Add Column

```sql
ALTER TABLE users
ADD COLUMN is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE;
```

### Remove Column

```sql
ALTER TABLE users
DROP COLUMN age;
```

### Count Rows

```sql
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users;
```

### Search Text (LIKE)

```sql
SELECT * FROM users
WHERE name LIKE '%cli%';
```

---

